detail.title: IBC Client Substitute
detail.description: Due to an unforeseen relayer issue that resulted in the subject client exceeding the trusting period, the IBC client 07-tendermint-55 used by channel-19 for IOV transfers from Starname to IRIShub is currently in an expired state. If accepted, this proposal will update client 07-tendermint-55 with the data from 07-tendermint-58 which is created newly, so that users may continue to take advantage of both the established channel.

detail.title: Starname 11: Chain Major Upgrade
detail.description:
Starname v0.11.6 : Production release

This version contains significant changes from all previous versions.

- Rebase from wasmd project
- Update to cosmos v0.45.9
- Update the IBC v3
- Starname modules: 
  - Add the escrow module
  - Add the burner module

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/iov-one/starnamed/compare/v0.29.2...v0.11.6

detail.title: Parameter changes for incress the number of validators
detail.description:
We want to increase the number of spots for validating our chain from 16 to 19.
This is important for the network because it's good for its health and its continued growth.
 We always have had a great active set of validators and we believe that the quality of the cosmos validators network can easily complement our active set with 3 new spots.
 One of these spots will be taken by our own Starname.me validator ran under the Starname company.
 This is also the first validator of a series of validators that will contribute to other  protocols of the Cosmos ecosystems.

detail.title: Token Burn 5 of 6 And The Next Software Upgrade
detail.description:
Prior to `iov-mainnet-ibc` (Stargate), token 'burns' sent tokens to blackhole\*iov where they remained locked until they were truly burned by the migration to `iov-mainnet-ibc`.  Locking tokens in blackhole\*iov is equivalent to a burn from the perspective of delegators and rewards; however, to new comers to the chain, blackhole\*iov appears to be a `whale` account that could sell the tokens at any time, which is not good.  Moreover, the total circulating supply reported on coingecko.com and coinmarketcap.com is not accurate when tokens are locked in blackhole\*iov.

  The technology to truly burn tokens sent to blackhole\*iov can be implemented and deployed with the next software upgrade, which should happen around the end of September, 2021.

  Vote `No` to keep Burn 5 of 6 tokens locked in the community fund until they can truly be burned and an accurate token circulating supply can be reported.

  Send the tokens to blackhole\*iov (https://big-dipper.iov-mainnet-ibc.iov.one/account/star1qqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqjewks3) where they will not be able to be truly burned, even with a software upgrade, by voting `Yes`.

  See https://medium.com/iov-internet-of-values/iov-token-donation-schedule-248f9ade08fc for details about the modernization of the Starname (IOV) chain tokenomics.

detail.title: Stargate Upgrade At Block 4,294,679 + 0% Inflation
detail.description:
Vote 'yes' to halt the Starname (IOV) blockchain `iov-mainnet-2` at block 4,294,679, export the state and migrate it to cosmos-sdk v0.42.4 (Stargate), set inflation to 0%, and start the migrated blockchain `iov-mainnet-ibc` at block 4,294,680 based on starnamed v0.10.12 (commit hash a92c6730de5ce25ce9cc01313409cc1d6f447327).
- See https://medium.com/iov-internet-of-values/what-apy-will-the-starname-iov-blockchain-have-when-inflation-is-0-5d623c6f0a27 for APY with 0% inflation
- See https://github.com/iov-one/starnamed/tree/master/scripts/genesis for the migration script

Block 4,294,679 is estimated to be committed on June 29, 2021 at approximately 8AM UTC.  If the migration does not succeed within 4 hours of the halt then `iov-mainnet-2` will be restarted.

detail.title: Change Unbonding Time + Enable IBC + Burn Tokens
detail.description:
Change unbonding time to 1,814,400,000,000,000 nanoseconds (21 days) in order to enable Inter-Blockchain Communication (IBC) so that IOV tokens will be tradeable on the Gravity DEX. Vote 'yes' to change the unbonding time, signal that validators should upgrade the network to cosmos-sdk v0.4x.x (Stargate), and burn the tokens in blackhole*iov (star1qqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqjewks3).

A subsequent proposal specifying the block height at which the migration to IBC should take place will follow.

detail.title: Token 'Burn' 4 of 6
detail.description:
Reduce the circulating supply of tokens by sending them to blackhole\*iov (star1qqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqqjewks3) where they can't be spent or delegated.  Tokens in account blackhole\*iov will be burned when the chain is upgraded to cosmos-sdk 0.4x.x (Stargate).

Why Does IOV Need To Modernize Its Tokenomics?

At inception, IOV SAS focused on blockchain innovation including developing the Weave SDK, IOV Core (now rolled into CosmJS), and even CosmWasm. The focus on innovation required significant allocations in the ICO token distribution for research and development, grants, tech incentives, bounties, and the like. In February, when Karim Ganem became CEO, IOV SAS pivoted to a business focus built on Starnames, which made the tokens earmarked for blockchain innovation difficult to justify. Hence the need to modernize.

Vote yes to burn the tokens.
